Name:		@FIX_CA_PACKAGE_NAME@
Version:	@FIX_CA_VERSION@
Release:	0
Summary:	A Gimp plugin for correcting chromatic aberration (CA)
License:	GPLv2+
Group:		Graphics/Editors and Converters
URL:		http://kcd.sourceforge.net/fix-ca.php
Source0:	https://github.com/JoesCat/gimp-fix-ca/releases/download/v%{version}/%{name}-dist-%{version}.tar.gz
BuildRequires:	autoconf
BuildRequires:	automake
BuildRequires:	gcc
BuildRequires:	make
BuildRequires:  gtk+2-devel
BuildRequires:  pkgconfig(gimp-2.0)
Requires:       gimp >= 2.6.0


%description
Fix-CA is a Gimp plug-in to correct chromatic aberration (CA).
Fix-CA is able to fix lateral CA caused by lens and colored fringing
caused by light travel through dense material such as glass and water
(which is called directional CA in the program).


%prep
%setup -q

%build
autoreconf -ivs
automake
%configure
%make_build


%install
%make_install


%files
